    Benchmarking ‘collections’

    benchmark.Rmd

    The goal of this document is to compare the performances of some of the existing packages. See benchmark.Rmd for the details.

    We are comparing these packages with collections.

    • dequer 2.0-1
    • datastructures 0.2.5
    • liqueueR 0.0.1
    • hash 2.2.6
    • hashmap 0.2.2

    Queue

    microbenchmark(
    dequer = test_dequer_queue_push_pop(100),
    datastructures = test_datastructures_queue_push_pop(100),
    liqueueR = test_liqueueR_queue_push_pop(100),
    collections = test_collections_queue_push_pop(100),
    times = 10,
    unit = "relative"
)
    ## Unit: relative
##            expr   min    lq   mean median    uq     max neval
##          dequer  1.00  1.00   1.00   1.00  1.00   1.000    10
##  datastructures 11.64 11.25 131.19   8.56  9.83 184.549    10
##        liqueueR 14.36 14.60   7.26  12.13 12.40   3.003    10
##     collections  2.34  2.38   1.22   1.99  2.32   0.688    10
    microbenchmark(
    dequer = test_dequer_queue_push_pop(10000),
    collections = test_collections_queue_push_pop(10000),
    times = 10,
    unit = "relative"
)
    ## Unit: relative
##         expr min   lq mean median   uq  max neval
##       dequer 6.6 8.26 7.37   7.75 7.51 6.18    10
##  collections 1.0 1.00 1.00   1.00 1.00 1.00    10

    OrderedDict

    microbenchmark(
    collections = test_collections_ordered_dict_set_get(100),
    collections_array = test_collections_ordered_dict_array_set_get(100),
    times = 10,
    unit = "relative"
)
    ## Unit: relative
##               expr  min   lq mean median   uq max neval
##        collections 1.47 1.45 1.48   1.46 1.46 1.5    10
##  collections_array 1.00 1.00 1.00   1.00 1.00 1.0    10

    collections = test_collections_ordered_dict_set_get(1000),
